The paper deals with mining associations in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social network analysis (cs.SOC) and data mining (cs.SD). The paper also discusses techniques for compressing and querying large datasets, which is relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The use of minhash signatures and locality sensitive hashing suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and similarity search. Overall, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.SD and cs.SOC.
